I agree, it is good idea to move not just `build()`, but also things that it uses.

However I don't know Flutter well enough to know what is useful to move. Some members obviously cannot be moved: fields assigned in the widget constructors, overridden members (except `build()`); something else? Can Flutter widgets have getters that just combine values of input fields, and are used outside of the Widget/State, by other widgets?

We could either try to move everything that can be moved, or we could trace what is transitively used from `build()` and can be moved.

For example, we could wither move `area`, or keep it in the widget. Again, I don't know if there even is such pattern in Flutter.

```dart
class MyWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  final int width;
  final int height;

  int get area => width * height;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return new Text('$width * $height');
  }
}
```

A related issue I haven't seen discussed above is that moving variables from the StatefulWidget class to the State class will make some of them not friendly to hot reload. Here is an example:

* Hot reload won't update the font size. 
```dart
class RandomWordsState extends State<RandomWords> {
  final _suggestions = <WordPair>[];
  final TextStyle _biggerFont = new TextStyle(fontSize: 18.0);
}
```

* Hot reload will update the font size. 
```dart
class RandomWords extends StatefulWidget {
  final TextStyle _biggerFont = new TextStyle(fontSize: 18.0);
  @override
  createState() => new RandomWordsState();
}
```

It's my opinion that if a variable is not supposed to change its value (e.g., _biggerFont) during the lifecycle of the widget, then it conceptually does not belong to the State class.

@InMatrix we have two related lints: http://dart-lang.github.io/linter/lints/prefer_const_constructors.html and http://dart-lang.github.io/linter/lints/prefer_const_declarations.html . There is no lint for exactly this situation (that the `final` field could be `static const`) AFAIK.

```dart
class A {
  const A();
}

class B {
  final A a = const A();
}
```
